Sure, here's the README documentation for the `VirtualTryOnApp` spec:

## Summary

The `VirtualTryOnApp` spec is a card that provides an AI-powered virtual clothing try-on experience. Users can select a model and outfit pieces, and the app will generate a photorealistic image of the model wearing the chosen clothing.

## Import

```javascript
import {
  VirtualTryOnApp,
  Model,
  Garment,
  TryOnResult
} from '../virtual-try-on-app';
```

## Usage as a Field

To use the `VirtualTryOnApp` spec as a field within a consuming card or field, you can add the following:

```json
{
  "type": "field",
  "name": "virtual-try-on",
  "field": {
    "type": "@cardstack/skills/Skill/VirtualTryOnApp",
    "model": {
      "type": "@cardstack/skills/Skill/Model",
      "id": "model-id"
    }
  }
}
```

In this example, the `virtual-try-on` field of the consuming card or field will display the `VirtualTryOnApp` functionality, with the specified `model` card linked to it.

## Template Usage

To invoke the `VirtualTryOnApp` spec within a consuming card or field's template, you can use the following:

```handlebars
<@cardstack/skills/Skill/VirtualTryOnApp
  @model={{this.model}}
/>
```

This will render the `VirtualTryOnApp` component within the consuming template, passing the `model` field as a parameter.
